<p class="">I am trying to put the facts clearly before the hon. Member, because I do not think that he is aware of them. The second point is that, this inducement having been given, people took advantage of it. One of their motives in taking advantage of it is obviously to take advantage of this concession.<p></p> The Finance Acts give this concession because, through the high rates of taxation, it would be uneconomic, or impossible, for employers to provide these schemes without the advantage given by the Finance Act. Therefore the answer is that one of the main purposes is to look after the employees, as every decent employer should, and the other purpose is to take advantage of the tax concession given by the Finance Act.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
