<p class="">I think I can oblige the hon. Gentleman by giving the name of my own firm. In this matter of superannuation funds there is a submission of an estimate from an insurance company under the group insurance scheme, and there set out, as part of the story, is the net cost; that is to say, the cost after taking Income Tax into consideration; and for the future it will be an aggregated sum of Income Tax and Profits Tax. The facts of that situation are, and will be, laid in front of every company that considers any superannuation fund at any time, and it is wholly academic and wholly stupid to say that the consideration of Income Tax is not a main factor in the decision to put a superannuation fund into force.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
