<p class="">I accept the right hon. and learned Gentleman's explanation. Suppose it has been decided that tax reduction is the main benefit, does it follow automatically that the reduction in liability for tax is deemed to be one of the main benefits of the transaction? <span id="2005" class="column-number" data-column-number="2005"></span> In such cases, it may be that the direction will not contain very full particulars. If it is the practice that the direction should contain most of what my hon. and learned Friend is asking, there would not be great harm in writing into the Clause, if not the actual words put forward, at least something similar.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
